The structural problem implicit is that ever fewer people working in positions above minimum wage inevitably translates to ever decreasing consumer demand. As this process intensifies there will be increasing disharmony as our societies must define and separate “needs” and “wants” and actually prioritize that which sustainable government revenue can provide and to whom.
